Package graph

package graph
  • Class
    Description
    Agent
    Represents an agent that can subscribe to topics, receive messages, and manage its own state.
    BinOpAgent
    Represents an agent that performs a binary operation on two input values and publishes the result to an output topic.
    Graph
    Represents a directed graph where nodes are topics and agents.
    IncAgent
    Represents an agent that increments a value received from an input topic and publishes the incremented value to an output topic.
    IndexAgent
    Represents an agent that indexes a list of strings based on an integer value and publishes the result to an output topic.
    Message
    Represents a message with various data representations.
    Node
    Represents a node in a graph with a name, a list of edges to other nodes, and a message.
    ParallelAgent
    Represents an agent that wraps another agent and processes callback messages in a separate thread to allow for parallel processing.
    PlusAgent
    Represents an agent that performs addition on values received from two input topics and publishes the result to an output topic.
    SortAgent
    Represents an agent that sorts a list of numeric values received from an input topic and publishes the sorted list to an output topic.
    Topic
    Represents a communication topic that manages subscribers and publishers, and facilitates the publishing of messages.
    TopicManagerSingleton
    Manages the creation and retrieval of Topic instances in a singleton pattern.
    TopicManagerSingleton.TopicManager
    Singleton class for managing topics.
